parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Steering Wheel Shake/Vibration at Highway Speeds
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The steering wheel shake or vibration at highway speeds can cause driver distraction, loss of control, and increased risk of accidents, especially if the vehicle pulls to one side.
symptoms: The steering wheel shakes or vibrates when driving at speeds between 65-80 mph
the steering wheel oscillates from left to right
the vibration can be felt and seen when hands are on the steering wheel
the vehicle pulls to one side (right or left) at all speeds
constant input from the driver is required to hold the car straight.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling or random shutdown can cause loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents, especially when driving on highways.
symptoms: The engine dies or shuts off while driving
and may occur at high speeds; all electronics may turn off before the shutdown; the vehicle may be unable to move after shutdown; the issue may occur randomly and intermittently.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the Adblue heater can cause the vehicle to fail emissions standards, leading to potential environmental harm and decreased vehicle performance.
symptoms: The check engine light illuminates; the vehicle may experience decreased performance; the Adblue heater may need to be replaced

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump can cause the vehicle to stall, which can lead to accidents, especially when driving at high speeds.
symptoms: The check engine light comes on
the fuel pump error code appears
metal debris is found in the fuel pump.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the AdBlue heating element can cause the vehicle to malfunction, leading to potential safety risks and costly repairs.
symptoms: The AdBlue heating element fails repeatedly
the vehicle may enter limp mode.
